message.content:
cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.EM (Embedded Systems) is the most likely category as the paper deals with resource-constrained embedded control systems.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a co-design of control and scheduling to maintain QoC guarantees in dynamic environments.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is another likely category as the paper uses a mobile robot target tracking system as a case study.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses fuzzy control technique to dynamically adjust the sampling periods of control loops.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a design methodology for the fuzzy feedback scheduling scheme.
